# 📚 Enqueue Operation (Queue Notes)

# What is Enqueue?

**Enqueue** is the operation of **inserting (adding) a new element into a queue**.

Since a queue follows **FIFO (First In, First Out)**, a new element is **always inserted at the Rear** of the queue.

> **Definition:** Enqueue means adding an element to the **rear (end)** of the queue.

---

# Visual Representation

Initially, the queue is:

```text
Front                Rear
  ↓                    ↓
+----+----+----+
| 10 | 20 | 30 |
+----+----+----+
```

Now perform:

```text
Enqueue(40)
```

After insertion:

```text
Front                     Rear
  ↓                         ↓
+----+----+----+----+
| 10 | 20 | 30 | 40 |
+----+----+----+----+
```

Notice that:

* Existing elements do **not move**.
* The new element is placed at the **rear**.
* The **rear pointer** moves to the new element.

---

# Step-by-Step Example

Initially:

```text
Queue = [ ]
Front = -1
Rear  = -1
```

### Step 1

```text
Enqueue(10)
```

```text
Front  Rear
  ↓      ↓
+----+
| 10 |
+----+
```

Queue:

```text
10
```

---

### Step 2

```text
Enqueue(20)
```

```text
Front        Rear
  ↓            ↓
+----+----+
| 10 | 20 |
+----+----+
```

Queue:

```text
10 20
```

---

### Step 3

```text
Enqueue(30)
```

```text
Front             Rear
  ↓                 ↓
+----+----+----+
| 10 | 20 | 30 |
+----+----+----+
```

Queue:

```text
10 20 30
```

---

### Step 4

```text
Enqueue(40)
```

```text
Front                  Rear
  ↓                      ↓
+----+----+----+----+
| 10 | 20 | 30 | 40 |
+----+----+----+----+
```

Queue:

```text
10 20 30 40
```

